# Project Summary

## Project Title
Healthcare Analytics Dashboard

## Objective
The objective of this project was to develop an interactive healthcare analytics dashboard using SQL and Power BI to explore patient demographics, admission patterns, medical conditions, and billing trends within a healthcare dataset.

## Tools Used
- Power BI
- SQL
- Excel
- GitHub

## Dataset Overview
The dataset included patient demographic information, admission details, medical conditions, billing amounts, hospital information, insurance providers, medications, and test results.

## Key Features
- Patient distribution analysis by gender
- Admission type comparison
- Medical condition analysis
- Monthly admission trend analysis
- Interactive gender filtering using slicers
- KPI monitoring for patient count and billing amount

## SQL Analysis
Basic SQL queries were used to:
- Count patient records
- Summarise medical conditions
- Analyse admission type distributions
- Explore healthcare trends within the dataset

## Dashboard Insights
- Patient distribution was approximately balanced between male and female groups.
- Admission types were relatively evenly distributed across elective, urgent, and emergency categories.
- Medical conditions showed similar representation across the dataset with minor variations between categories.
- Monthly admission trends fluctuated throughout the year, with higher admission counts observed during mid-year months.
- Total billing amounts exceeded 1 billion, highlighting substantial healthcare expenditure within the dataset.

## Skills Demonstrated
- Data cleaning and preparation
- SQL querying and aggregation
- Interactive dashboard development
- KPI reporting and visualisation
- Trend analysis
- Data storytelling and insight communication
- GitHub project organisation

## Project Status
Completed portfolio project developed for analytics and business intelligence skill development.
